<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1436,1836,1971]" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">
The status of the types of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lansberge" authorityYear="1879" box="[436,636,1836,1862]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Rhopaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aruensis">
<emphasis box="[436,636,1836,1862]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">Rhopaea aruensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not clear. It was described from an unknown number of males and females from the Aru Islands, 
<collectingCountry box="[466,575,1872,1898]" name="Indonesia" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
and listed as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Arrow" authorityYear="1941" baseAuthorityName="Waterhouse" baseAuthorityYear="1875" box="[884,1042,1872,1898]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Dermolepida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albohirtum">
<emphasis box="[884,1042,1872,1898]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">D. albohirtum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Britton, E. B." box="[1083,1247,1872,1899]" pageId="32" pageNumber="483" pagination="51 - 59" refId="ref25095" refString="Britton, E. B. (1957) A revision of the genus Dermolepida (Coleoptera: Melolonthinae). Proceedings of the Royal Entomological Society of London B, 26, 51 - 59. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.1957. tb 01509. x" type="journal article" year="1957">Britton (1957)</bibRefCitation>
. However, direct examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[369,467,1909,1935]" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">syntypes</typeStatus>
(in IRSB) by James Harrison (University of the Witwatersrand, personal communication) and through images by me suggests that it may represent a different species. This requires further study.
</paragraph>
